# Code Style Guide

## Goal

This document defines code and writing expectations that help keep the repository understandable for both humans and AI agents.

## General Principles

- Prefer compatibility with the existing repository style.
- Keep responsibilities separated and explicit.
- Favor small, explainable changes over unrelated refactors.
- Keep naming stable and consistent.
- Document business constraints, edge cases, and non-obvious decisions.

## Structure Rule

- For new projects, a recommended structure such as `internal/app` may be adopted.
- For existing projects, document and respect the structure already in use before suggesting changes.

## Documentation Rule

- New behavior should leave behind documentation where future contributors will look first.
- Shared rules belong in shared documents, not only in task-specific notes.
